What is an object in Java?
An object in Java is an instance of a class that represents a real-world entity and contains state, behavior, and identity.
That means:
•	A class is a blueprint
•	An object is the real thing created from that blueprint
________________________________________
An object has:
1.	State → data (variables / fields)
2.	Behavior → methods (functions)
3.	Identity → unique reference in memory
________________________________________
Example 
class Car 
{ }      // class (blueprint)
Car c = new Car(); // object (instance)

What keyword is used to create an object in Java?
Ans: The keyword new is used to create an object in Java.
