Quick check 🧠
If a thread is a daemon, what happens when all non-daemon threads finish?
(Answer in one line)
It will still run.
Not quite — here’s the clarification:
•	If a thread is a daemon thread, the J7VM does not wait for it to finish.
•	As soon as all non-daemon threads finish, the JVM exits, and any remaining daemon threads stop immediately.
✅ So a daemon thread may not complete if only daemon threads are left.
